{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}} {{Infobox person | name = Franz Humer | image = | caption = | birth_name = Franz Bernhard Humer | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1946|07|01}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | residence = | nationality = Swiss-Austrian | ethnicity = | education = | alma_mater = | occupation = Businessman | years_active = 1967–present | salary = | title = Chairman of [[Hoffmann-La Roche|Roche]] and [[Diageo]] plc | term = 2008–2017 | predecessor = [[James Blyth, Baron Blyth of Rowington|James Blyth]] | successor = [[Javier Ferrán]] | boards = Roche, Diageo, [[Citigroup]], [[International Centre for Missing & Exploited Children]] (ICMEC; Chairman) | spouse = | children = }}
'''Franz Bernhard Humer''' (born 1 July 1946)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dellam.com/cgi-bin/main.pl|title=Franz Humer search|date=|work=Dellam|accessdate=3 November 2012}}</ref> is a Swiss-Austrian businessman, the chairman of [[Diageo]], and of [[Hoffmann-La Roche|Roche]].
==Business career== Humer was the chairman of Swiss pharmaceutical company [[Hoffmann-La Roche|Roche]]<ref>[http://www.roche.com/de/about_roche/management/board_of_directors/board_of_directors-dr_franz_b._humer Franz Humer] in: Roche, 13 August 2013</ref> and chairman of [[Diageo]] plc, a British multinational alcoholic beverages company, the world's largest producer of spirits and a major producer of beer and wine.
[[Javier Ferrán]] will be the next chairman of Diageo, from 1 January 2017, when Humer retires.<ref name="cityam">{{cite web|url=http://www.cityam.com/241353/diageo-appoints-javier-ferran-new-chairman-of-the-board-|publisher=cityam.com|title=Diageo appoints new chairman of the board, Javier Ferran, who will take over from Dr Franz Humer from 2017 &#124; City A.M.|accessdate=10 September 2016}}</ref><ref name="bloomberg">{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-05-18/diageo-says-javier-ferran-to-replace-chairman-franz-humer|publisher=bloomberg.com|title=Diageo Says Javier Ferran to Replace Chairman Franz Humer - Bloomberg|accessdate=10 September 2016}}</ref>
Humer was chairman of [[Reed Elsevier]] from July 2008 to September 2010, when he was succeeded by [[Anthony Habgood]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/franz-humer/ | title=Franz Humer profile|publisher=Forbes |date=|accessdate=31 October 2012}}</ref>
==Philanthropy== [[File:ICMEC Board.jpg|thumb|300px|Franz Humer, Chairman, (''top row, second from end on far right'') with the board of directors of the [[International Centre for Missing & Exploited Children]]]] Humer is chairman of the [[International Centre for Missing & Exploited Children]], a global nonprofit organization that combats [[child sexual exploitation]], [[child pornography]], and [[child abduction]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.icmec.org/missingkids/servlet/PageServlet?LanguageCountry=en_X1&PageId=1225 |title=ICMEC Board Members |work=icmec.org |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150703182150/http://www.icmec.org/missingkids/servlet/PageServlet?LanguageCountry=en_X1&PageId=1225 |archivedate=3 July 2015 |df=dmy }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nzz.ch/aktuell/feuilleton/uebersicht/eine-stimme-fuer-missbrauchte-kinder-1.18215155|title=Schutz, Hilfe, Prävention: Eine Stimme für missbrauchte Kinder|date=6 January 2014|work=Neue Zürcher Zeitung}}</ref> Humer is chairman at the [[INSEAD]] school of business.
