{{BLP sources|date=May 2017}} {{EngvarB|date=September 2013}} {{Use dmy dates|date=September 2013}} {{Infobox person | name = Narendra Maharjan | image = Narendra Maharjan.jpg | caption = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1966|12|10}} | birth_place = [[Hetauda]], [[Makwanpur]], [[Nepal]] | nationality = Nepali | citizenship = Nepali | occupation = Producer, Distributor, Exhibitor and Actor | spouse = {{marriage|[[Sita Kumari Shrestha]]|2005}} | children = (2 Son) Shanshak Man Singh Shaswat Man Singh | parents = Nand Bahadur Maharjan Parvati Maharjan | relatives = [[Surendra Man Sigh]] (Karma Brother Band) | imagesize = | yearsactive = 2005–present }}
'''Narendra Maharjan''' is a movie producer, distributor, exhibitor, and actor. He is President of distribution company FD, and produced movies like [[First Love (2010 Nepali film)|First Love]]<ref>{{Cite journal|date=2017-05-02|title=First Love (2010 Nepali film)|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=First_Love_(2010_Nepali_film)&oldid=778363336|journal=Wikipedia|language=en}}</ref> (2010), [[Loot 2|Loot]] <ref>{{Cite journal|date=2017-06-24|title=Loot (2012 film)|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Loot_(2012_film)&oldid=787254286|journal=Wikipedia|language=en}}</ref>(2012), [[Chhadke]] (2013), [[Mission Paisa Reloaded]] (2015), Fanko (2016).
== Early life == Narendra Maharjan was born on 10 December 1966. His father is Nand Bahadur Maharjan of Bhutandevi Mandir Road, [[Hetauda]] ward no 10, [[Makwanpur District]], Nepal. He completed his school from Tribhuvan Hanuman Higher Secondary School ([[Birgunj]]) and college from Thakurram Multiple college ([[Birgunj]]).
== Career == Narendra Maharjan started his career as distributor of Hindi movies [[Aag (2007 film)|Aag]] and [[Krantiveer]] in [[Nepal]], Later on He co-produced the movies Maute Dai, Dulaha Raja, Dulahi Rani, Dharmaputra, Dhansampati, Upahar, Sukha Dukha, He also a chairman of the FD Company Pvt. Ltd. in 2012 which distribute 90% of the movies produced in Nepal all over the country.
He is also operating six cinema exhibition centers in different part of the country where he holds a position of chairperson in Bina Chalchitra Mandir, a coordinator and a share holder in OM and OMAX Chalchitra Mandir and is a contractor of Janajyoti Chalchitra Mandir, Satya Chalchitra Mandir and JiwanDeep Chalchitra Mandir.
He is also Involved with the professional organizations where he hold the position of Central member in Nepal Motion Picture Association<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nepalhomepage.com/community-and-social-services/trade-associations/nepal-motion-picture-association.html|title=Nepal Motion Picture Association - Nepal Home Page|date=2005-10-18|work=Nepal Home Page|access-date=2017-08-18|language=en-US}}</ref> and Pro-Public Cineworkers Association Nepal and as a member in Nepal National Commerce Association and Nepal Motion Picture Producer Association
